# Typography Rules

- Keep typography lightweight, readable, and consistent across the site.
- Use one primary sans-serif font stack for the whole UI.
- Use one monospace font only for code, wallet addresses, transaction hashes, token mints, and technical values.
- Do not introduce decorative fonts.
- Do not load Google Fonts at runtime from external URLs.
- Prefer system font stack or self-hosted WOFF2 fonts.
- If using custom fonts, load only required weights: 400, 500, and 600.
- Do not load unused weights, italic variants, or multiple font families.

## Font Usage

- Body text must use normal weight and comfortable line-height.
- Headings must use `font-semibold` and `tracking-tight`.
- Avoid `font-extrabold`, `font-black`, and aggressive display typography unless explicitly needed for a hero section.
- Use `font-medium` for labels, navigation items, FAQ questions, and compact UI titles.
- Use monospace only for technical identifiers, not for general UI text.

## Type Scale

- Sidebar items: `text-sm`
- Navbar items: `text-sm`
- Form labels: `text-sm font-medium`
- Form helper text: `text-xs leading-5`
- Form input text: `text-base sm:text-sm`
- Body text: `text-base leading-7`
- Intro text: `text-base sm:text-lg`
- Card titles: `text-base` or `text-lg font-semibold`
- Section headings: `text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- Page H1: `text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- Hero H1: maximum `text-4xl sm:text-5xl`, only on major landing pages.

## Color and Contrast

- Use high-contrast neutral text colors.
- Light mode:
  - Primary text: `text-zinc-950`
  - Body text: `text-zinc-600` or `text-zinc-700`
  - Muted text: `text-zinc-500`
- Dark mode:
  - Primary text: `dark:text-zinc-50`
  - Body text: `dark:text-zinc-300` or `dark:text-zinc-400`
  - Muted text: `dark:text-zinc-500`
- Do not use low-contrast text for important instructions, warnings, fees, or transaction details.

## Layout and Readability

- Long text blocks must use `max-w-3xl` or similar readable width.
- Body paragraphs should use `leading-7`.
- Avoid very wide text lines.
- Avoid center-aligning long paragraphs.
- Use left-aligned text for tool descriptions, FAQs, warnings, and form guidance.
- Use consistent spacing between headings and body text.

## Sidebar Typography

- Sidebar category labels must use `text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide`.
- Sidebar links must use `text-sm`.
- Active sidebar links may use `font-medium`.
- Do not use large typography inside the sidebar.

## Forms

- Labels must use `text-sm font-medium`.
- Helper text must use `text-xs leading-5`.
- Error text must use `text-xs` with clear color contrast.
- Inputs should use `text-base sm:text-sm` to avoid mobile browser zoom issues.
- Form section titles should use `text-base font-semibold`.

## SEO Content

- Tool pages must include visible, readable HTML typography for H1, intro, requirements, fee explanation, safety notes, FAQ, and related tools.
- Do not place SEO text only inside React islands.
- Static content must remain readable without JavaScript.

## Restrictions

- Do not add new typography libraries without approval.
- Do not add animation libraries for text effects.
- Do not use text gradients for important content.
- Do not use tiny text below `text-xs`.
- Do not use uppercase for long labels or paragraphs.
